Experiment III 
Objective: Introduction to Docker, Writing Docker files, Building and running 
Docker containers.  
Required Software / Tools: Docker Desktop, Python, VSCode. 
Procedure: 
I. Install Docker Desktop 
1. Download docker desktop from official Docker Website as per your O.S. or 
download from the Store. 
https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/  
2. Click the executable file and proceed with installation steps.  
3. Once installed, open the docker desktop app and register with your email. 
 
 
4. Verify your email to complete the installation. 
 
5. Open and validate Docker desktop is running fine. Fix if any issues. 
 
 
 
II. Containerization Python application using Docker: 
1. Open VSCode and Create and open a New Folder with name Exp3. 
2. In VSCode, under Exp3, create file “requirements.txt” with following contents: 
flask==2.3.2 
3. Create app.py with below contents: 
from flask import Flask 
app = Flask(__name__) 
@app.route("/") 
def home(): 
return "Hello, Dockerized Flask App!" 
if __name__ == "__main__": 
app.run(host="0.0.0.0", port=5000) 
4. Now create one more file with name “Dockerfile” with following contents: 
# Use official Python image 
FROM python:3.9-slim 
# Set working directory 
WORKDIR /app 
# Copy application files 
COPY app.py . 
COPY requirements.txt . 
# Install dependencies 
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt 
# Expose port 
EXPOSE 5000 
# Run the app 
CMD ["python", "app.py"] 
5. Build the docker Image by running below command from terminal: 
docker build -t flask-web-app . 
6. Run the Container by running below command: 
docker run -d -p 5000:5000 --name flask-container flask-web-app 
7. Validate from Docker desktop if container is running and also verify application 
from the browser: 
http://localhost:5000/  
8. Stop the container, using below steps: 
a. docker ps 
b. docker stop flask-container 
c. docker rm flask-container 
d.  docker ps 
